# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# PII / Raw POS data — NEVER commit these
# Raw exports from Des's till may contain transaction IDs, staff names,
# payment card fragments, or customer-identifiable information.
# Only the aggregated hourly CSV (data/synthetic/odonoghues_hourly.csv
# or its real-data replacement) and features.parquet are safe to commit.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
data/raw/pos_*/
data/raw/*pos*.csv
data/raw/*pos*.xlsx
data/raw/*export*.csv
data/raw/*export*.xlsx
data/raw/*transactions*.csv
data/raw/*transactions*.xlsx
data/raw/*till*.csv
data/raw/*till*.xlsx
data/raw/*sales_detail*.csv
data/raw/*payments*.csv
data/raw/*staff*.csv
data/raw/des_*.csv
data/raw/des_*.xlsx
# Catch-all: any file dropped directly into data/raw that isn't one of the
# known public-data files managed by refresh_data.py
# (footfall, weather, enrichment, events, holidays etc. are fine to commit)
*.raw_pos
*.pos_export
